Nautilus developers are actively working on one of the project repositories, /usr/src/kodekloudrepos/news. Recently, they decided to implement some new features in the application, and they want to maintain those new changes in a separate branch. 
Below are the requirements that have been shared with the DevOps team:

On Storage server in Stratos DC create a new branch xfusioncorp_news from master branch in /usr/src/kodekloudrepos/news git repo.

Please do not try to make any changes in the code.

Solutions:-

Access the Storage Server:

Connect to the Stratos DC storage server where the repository is located.

Navigate to the Repository:

Change your directory to the repository location:
cd /usr/src/kodekloudrepos/news

Create the New Branch:
Ensure you are on the master branch:
git checkout master

Create a new branch named xfusioncorp_news from the master branch
git checkout -b xfusioncorp_news

